    "Our 'deterministic' strategy uses a temperature of 0.0, top-p of 0.9, and when possible, a repetition penalty of 1.",
    "We chose this deterministic decoding strategy to obtain predictable and consistent results across samples, which is crucial for benchmarking where accuracy and reliability are emphasized.. Deterministic decoding is most important for tasks common in finance such as data extraction or structured text generation due to the improved performance from low temperatures (Liang et al., 2024; Zarrieß et al., 2021)",
